## Variables and tokens

- **Names encode meaning**, not only value — agents need to bind `#0055FF` to **role** via variable path/name (in **semantic** collections), or to **hue + shade** in **primitives**.
- **Modes and collections** — Structure so **mode** (light/dark, platform) is consistent; avoid duplicating the same semantic under unrelated labels.
- **No synonym sprawl** — Same semantic → same path pattern across files when possible.

### Rule 1 — Primitive colors: name the **pigment**, not the **meaning**

- In **`Primitive` / `Colors/…`**, tokens describe **chroma** (hue + shade or alpha): e.g. `Colors/neutral/neutral-500`, `Colors/yellow/yellow-600`.
- **Do not** encode product semantics in **`Colors/…`** paths: no `primary`, `success`, `button`, `card`, `destructive`, etc. as folder or leaf names under primitives. Product roles are expressed in **`Display mode`** as **`VARIABLE_ALIAS`** paths — **not** under a separate **`{Category}/Semantics/`** tree: neutral tokens use **`Defaults`**; chromatic / component roles use **`{Category}/Components/{Component}/…`** when that published component (or its brief) introduces them.
- When docs say “primary uses *500*”, that means the **Display mode** alias resolves to something like **`{hue}-500`**, not a primitive named `Colors/primary/…`.

### Color tokens — `Primitive` vs `Display mode` (`Defaults` + `Components` only)

| Layer | Collection | What to encode | Examples |
|--------|------------|----------------|----------|
| **Primitive** | `Primitive` / `Colors/…` | **Chroma only** — hue + scale step or alpha. **No** product role, component, or state in the path. | `Colors/blue/blue-500`, `Colors/neutral/neutral-800` |
| **Neutral transverse** | `Display mode` | **`Defaults` only** under each category root — neutral UI (high / middle / low, etc.) plus **Constant** / **Constant inverse** pairs for text & icons. **Do not** create **`Texts/Semantics/…`**, **`Surfaces/Semantics/…`**, or parallel **`Semantics`** folders for a “global semantic” layer at token bootstrap. | `Texts/Defaults/text-high`, `Icons/Defaults/icon-high`, `Borders/Defaults/border-high`, `Surfaces/Defaults/surface-high` |
| **Component-scoped** | `Display mode` | **All** non-neutral color roles tied to shipped UI: chrome, states, **and** chromatic roles (`primary`, `success`, …) **when** the **published** component needs them — **`{Category}/Components/{Component}/…`**. Still **aliases** to `Primitive` colors only — no raw hex. | `Surfaces/Components/Button/surface-button-primary`, `Texts/Components/Button/text-button-label`, `Borders/Components/Button/border-button-primary-focus` |

**Classification (no mixed “Components” root):** Tokens under **`Components`** are **sorted under the visual category** — `Texts/`, `Icons/`, `Borders/`, `Surfaces/`, `Backgrounds/`. Each category gets its own `Components/{Component}/` subtree when that component consumes a color there (e.g. button label under `Texts/Components/Button/`, button fill under `Surfaces/Components/Button/`).

**Path pattern (component layer):** `{Category}/Components/{Component}/{prefix}-{component-kebab}-{role}[-{state}]`

- **`{Component}`** — PascalCase, matches the published component name (`Button`, `TextField`).
- **`{component-kebab}`** — kebab-case in the **token leaf** (`button`, `text-field`).
- **`{prefix}`** — must match category: `text-`, `icon-`, `border-`, `surface-`, `background-`.
- **`{state}`** — optional suffix: `hover`, `pressed`, `disabled`, `focus`, `selected`, etc. (team glossary).

**Scalability and workflow:** The pattern applies to **all** components in the library. **Do not** pre-create `Components/…` tokens for every component in an initial token pass unless the brief requires it; add **incrementally** when a **published** component needs a dedicated color. Prefer reusing the **same** `Primitive` (or the same **`Defaults`** alias) when appearance matches; add **`Components/{Component}/…`** tokens when the role is **non-reusable** as neutral default or is **owned by that component**.

---

## Text and content properties

- Name by **semantic role**: `Label`, `Title`, `Sub`, `Value`, `Input` (placeholder copy) — not `Text` / `String1` unless truly generic.

---

## Positions and repeated slots

- **Left / right**: **`L`** / **`R`** with a **space** — `Icon L`, `Icon R`, `Action L`, `Action R`.
- **Multiple similar actions**: **`Action 1`**, **`Action 2`**, **`Action 3`** (arabic numerals).

---

## Instance swap

- Label the **slot**: `Content`, `Left content`, or token/theme slots like `Lighting` → nested swap (`neutral`).
- If a swap applies only when a boolean is on, **nest** the swap under that boolean; the swap describes **what** is swapped, not “instance”.

---

## Groups and nesting (component properties)

- Group related props (`Content`, `Status`, `Selector`, `Footer`, `HEADER` / `FOOTER`).
- **Avoid** dev-style group names with a **leading dot** or raw **camelCase** in published components (e.g. `.headerDrawer`) — use readable **Title Case** (`Header`, `Header drawer`).

---

## Checklist (shipping / audit)

- [ ] Names favor **objects + roles** where the UI is domain-specific; primitives stay generic.
- [ ] **Property labels** and variant values use **Title Case** consistently; **no synonym drift** for the same concept.
- [ ] **Booleans**: **A** (chrome) = **noun** toggles; **B** (domain) = **`Can` / `Has`** (or agreed capability pattern).
- [ ] **Left/right** use **`L` / `R`** with space; stacked actions use **`Action N`**.
- [ ] **Text props** use **roles** (`Label`, `Title`, `Sub`, …).
- [ ] **States/modes** exist beyond the happy path where the product has them.
- [ ] **Variables** and **components** use **predictable paths** and **one vocabulary** for agents to search and bind.
- [ ] **Primitive** color names are **hue/value** only (**Rule 1**); **`Display mode`** uses **`Defaults`** (neutral + Constant / Constant inverse) and **`{Category}/Components/{Component}/…`** for component-owned and chromatic roles — **no** **`Semantics`** folder layer; **component-scoped** paths stay under **`Texts` / `Icons` / `Borders` / `Surfaces` / `Backgrounds`**, added incrementally when the component ships.
